Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 4 (KCNA) -- The government of the 
Republic of Equatorial Guinea in a statement on February 23 
supported the stand of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea 
towards the nuclear issue of the Korean peninsula. 
  It said: "Considering the attempts of the western powers to 
coercively solve the nuclear issue of the Korean peninsula to be 
a big threat to the peace and security of the world, hoping for 
the further development of the bonds of friendship and 
cooperation with the Democratic People's Republic of Korea in 
line with the principles of international laws and holding that 
the nuclear issue of the Korean peninsula arousing a deep 
concern of mankind must be solved in a peaceful way as far as 
possible, the government of the Republic of Equatorial Guinea 
supports all the proposals and measures put forward by the DPRK 
Government and advises the United States of America to accept 
the proposals of the DPRK Government." 

